addEVstation(uint256,bytes32,bytes32,byt.details: Use the emitted LogEVstationAdded event to get the new evStation's generated IDfurther the evStation must belong to the evUtility -- how to ensure this?

params._city: city where the evStation is located
params._uId: ID of the evUtility; the evUtility must be owned by the caller!

params._uName: Name of the evUtility, must be unique (transaction will fail otherwise)
params._uOwner: Address of the evUtility owner, can be any Ethereum address

params._newType: New Charger type for the evStation
params._sId: ID of the evStation that is being changed (ID itself does not change)

params._newUName: New name of the evUtility, must be unique or remain unchanged
params._uId: ID of the evUtility that is being changed (ID itself does not change)

evUtilityExists(bytes32).details: Useful for input validation both in the contract and in the frontend
evUtilityExists(bytes32).return: true if name exists, false otherwise

findVacantEVStations(bytes32,bytes32,uin.return: array of evStations where slot is vacant at desired time.

params._index: Index of the item to get (the N)

getEVstationCount().details: Use it in the frontend to iterate over evStations

getEVstationCount(uint256).details: Use it in the frontend to iterate over evStations

params.uId: Id of evUtility for which the the number of stations are required

getEVstationsCount(uint256).details: Use it in the frontend to iterate over evStations by evUtility
getEVstationsCount(uint256).return: The number of evStation owned by the evUtility

getEVutilityCount().details: Use it in the frontend to iterate over evUtilities

isOwner().return: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

devdoc.title: Electric Vehicles Charging marketplace for car owners and service providers

addEVstation(uint256,bytes32,bytes32,byt.notice: Add an evStation to the list

addEVutility(bytes32,address,string).notice: Add an EVutility to the list

evUtilityExists(bytes32).notice: Check if the evUtility name is taken or not

findVacantEVStations(bytes32,bytes32,uin.notice: Finds evStations where charging slots are vacant at desired time

getCost(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Calculate cost of charging the vehicle.

getEVstationByEVutility(uint256,uint256).notice: Get N-th evStation of a given evKioiskChain

getEVstationById(uint256).notice: Get a certain evStation by its ID

getEVstationCount().notice: Get the number of evStations stored

getEVstationCount(uint256).notice: Get the number of evStations stored for given uId (evUtility)

getEVstationsCount(uint256).notice: Get the number of evStations from a given evUtility

getEVutilityById(uint256).notice: Get a certain evUtility by its ID

getEVutilityCount().notice: Get the number of evUtilities stored

getEnergyRate(uint256).notice: Energy rate of the station where the vehicle is charged. Do it via Oracle

getLocationRate(uint256).notice: Location rate of the station where the vehicle is charged. Do it via Oracle

getSlotById(uint256).notice: Get a certain slot by its ID

isStationVacant(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Tests if evStation is vacant at given time

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
